result.execSummary:
The defendant Tanner Jess Rix was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tanner Jess Rix is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tanner Jess Rix was found guilty of Hiding a Corpse [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.11(2).

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael E. Nieskes, DF ATTY: Brian Thomas Smestad,  ATTY: Alex Andrea DF: Tanner Jess Rix appeared from jail.  Court called at 1:07 p.m.  Includes 14CF400 (Plea/Sentencing) & 15CF122.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Attorney Andrea recites the agreement.  Attorney Nieskes advises the court the DE has made a statement to Wabasha County admitting to the homicide taking place in Minnesota.  Attorneys are asking the court to set out sentencing for 6 months to allow for Minnesota to prosecute the DE with regards to the homicide.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads No Contest to Ct 2 (with the repeater stricken) in 14CF400.  Attorney's stipulate to the facts.  Court finds factual basis and Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.   Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct  2 (with the repeater stricken) in 14CF400. On motion of the State,  Ct 1 held open and Ct. 3 & Ct. 4 without prejudice in 14CF400.  Court reserves on a PSI at this time.  Court modifies Bail Bond to a $100,000 signature bond.  

In 15CF122 DE waives his right to extradition back to Minnesota.  Court questions the DE.  Crt finds the DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights to challenge extradition.  DE signs extradition documents.  DE to be held without bond. Court adjourned at 1:33 p.m. lw
